SB 1538
1 (a) “Health or safety emergency” includes law enforcement efforts to locate a child who
2 may be a victim of kidnap, abduction or custodial interference and law enforcement or child
3 protective services efforts to respond to a report of child abuse or neglect pursuant to ORS
4 419B.005 to 419B.050.
5 (b) “Law enforcement” does not include a federal immigration authority as that term is
6 defined in ORS 180.805.
7 [(1)] (2) A public school or school district shall disclose personally identifiable information or
8 other information allowed to be disclosed by the federal Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act
9 from an education record of a student to:
10 (a) Law enforcement, child protective services and health care professionals in connection with
11 a health or safety emergency if knowledge of the information is necessary to protect the health and
12 safety of the student or other individuals; and
13 (b) Courts and state and local juvenile justice agencies including[, but not limited to,] law
14 enforcement agencies, juvenile departments and child protective service agencies. Disclosure under
15 this paragraph must relate to the court’s or juvenile justice agency’s ability to serve the needs of
16 a student prior to the student’s adjudication under ORS chapter 419C. A person to whom personally
17 identifiable information is disclosed under this paragraph shall certify, in writing, that the person
18 will not disclose the information to a third party other than another court or juvenile justice agency
19 or a person or organization providing direct services to the student on behalf of a juvenile justice
20 agency.
21 [(2) As used in this section, a “health or safety emergency” includes, but is not limited to, law
22 enforcement efforts to locate a child who may be a victim of kidnap, abduction or custodial interference
23 and law enforcement or child protective services efforts to respond to a report of child abuse or neglect
24 pursuant to ORS 419B.005 to 419B.050.]
25 (3) A person who receives information under this section is not liable civilly or criminally for
26 failing to disclose the information.
